<p>The <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+421">Offset on Plane</span> command enables you to create plane offset curves. An offset curve is a curve whose distance from a selected curve is constant at all points.</p>


<p id="HIDEP">Note that this command is available only in the <span class="UI_OPTION" id="eklib.msg+eklib+422">Model</span> and <a href="mk:@MSITStore:prf.chm::/language/sketcher/FWfile/T_FW_sk_01.htm"><span class="UI_OPTION" id="eklib.msg+eklib+558">2D Profile</span></a> modes and not in the <a href="mk:@MSITStore:prf.chm::/language/sketcher/FWfile/T_FW_3D_sk.htm"><span class="UI_OPTION" id="eklib.msg+eklib+559">3D Profile</span></a> mode.</p>

<p>An <i>offset curve of a plane curve on its placement plane</i> is constructed by moving each point by a given distance (the offset distance) along the normal to the curve.</p>

